{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "interpreted-shaft",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# VAMPNets on Alanine Dipeptide\n",
    "\n",
    "This example we study the Alanine Dipeptide molecule. Alanine Dipeptide is an example for a small peptide exhibiting rare-events in solution at room temperature. The $\\phi$ and $\\psi$ dihedral angles of the molecule have been identified as the two relevant coordinates for the slowest kinteic processes of the system under equilibrium conditions. \n",
    "\n",
    "Here we seek to recover these relevant coordinates from $(x,y,z)$ atom position data using VAMPNets. To this end, we require a working installation of [PyTorch](https://pytorch.org/) as well as [mdshare](https://markovmodel.github.io/mdshare/) to obtain the data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "working-tampa",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:16.461097Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:15.918682Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "import mdshare  # for trajectory data\n",
    "\n",
    "from tqdm.notebook import tqdm  # progress bar"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "invalid-digit",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we set up the device. If available, we use CUDA."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "tough-application",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:16.468784Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:16.466422Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if torch.cuda.is_available():\n",
    "    device = torch.device(\"cuda\")\n",
    "    torch.backends.cudnn.benchmark = True\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    device = torch.device(\"cpu\")\n",
    "torch.set_num_threads(12)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "defensive-hacker",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Obtain the data via mdshare:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "ranking-reviewer",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:16.968600Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:16.841730Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "ala_coords_file = mdshare.fetch(\n",
    "    \"alanine-dipeptide-3x250ns-heavy-atom-positions.npz\", working_directory=\"data\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "with np.load(ala_coords_file) as fh:\n",
    "    data = [fh[f\"arr_{i}\"].astype(np.float32) for i in range(3)]\n",
    "\n",
    "dihedral_file = mdshare.fetch(\n",
    "    \"alanine-dipeptide-3x250ns-backbone-dihedrals.npz\", working_directory=\"data\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "with np.load(dihedral_file) as fh:\n",
    "    dihedral = [fh[f\"arr_{i}\"] for i in range(3)]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "arbitrary-parade",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Since the dynamics of the molecule are completely described by its position in the dihedral plane, we can use these two variables to visualize the state population."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "opponent-butter",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:17.759755Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:17.480917Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1)\n",
    "hb = ax.hexbin(*np.concatenate(dihedral).T, mincnt=5)\n",
    "ax.set_aspect('equal')\n",
    "cb = f.colorbar(hb, ax=ax)\n",
    "cb.set_label('# of frames in bin')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "psychological-appeal",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's define the dataset that we use for training and validation. We use a lagtime $\\tau=1$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "least-piece",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:18.839349Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:18.537511Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from deeptime.data import TimeLaggedDataset\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset = TimeLaggedDataset.from_trajectories(lagtime=1, data=data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "religious-sugar",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we split the data into training and validation set."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "impressed-hartford",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:21.797964Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:21.739958Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_val = int(len(dataset)*.3)\n",
    "train_data, val_data = torch.utils.data.random_split(dataset, [len(dataset) - n_val, n_val])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "delayed-cursor",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we can set up the VAMPNet lobe(s)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "minor-immunology",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:39.566621Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:39.543739Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Sequential(\n",
      "  (0): BatchNorm1d(30, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True)\n",
      "  (1): Linear(in_features=30, out_features=30, bias=True)\n",
      "  (2): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (3): Linear(in_features=30, out_features=100, bias=True)\n",
      "  (4): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (5): Linear(in_features=100, out_features=100, bias=True)\n",
      "  (6): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (7): Linear(in_features=100, out_features=100, bias=True)\n",
      "  (8): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (9): Linear(in_features=100, out_features=100, bias=True)\n",
      "  (10): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (11): Linear(in_features=100, out_features=100, bias=True)\n",
      "  (12): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (13): Linear(in_features=100, out_features=100, bias=True)\n",
      "  (14): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (15): Linear(in_features=100, out_features=30, bias=True)\n",
      "  (16): ELU(alpha=1.0)\n",
      "  (17): Linear(in_features=30, out_features=6, bias=True)\n",
      "  (18): Softmax(dim=1)\n",
      ")\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "lobe = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "    nn.BatchNorm1d(data[0].shape[1]),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(data[0].shape[1], 30), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(30, 100), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(100, 100), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(100, 100), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(100, 100), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(100, 100), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(100, 100), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(100, 30), nn.ELU(),\n",
    "    nn.Linear(30, 6),\n",
    "    nn.Softmax(dim=1)  # obtain fuzzy probability distribution over output states\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "from copy import deepcopy\n",
    "lobe_timelagged = deepcopy(lobe).to(device=device)\n",
    "lobe = lobe.to(device=device)\n",
    "print(lobe)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "revolutionary-boulder",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With the lobe defined, we can create a VAMPNet estimator."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "imported-depth",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:42.126023Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:42.118434Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from deeptime.decomposition.deep import VAMPNet\n",
    "\n",
    "vampnet = VAMPNet(lobe=lobe, lobe_timelagged=lobe_timelagged, learning_rate=5e-4, device=device)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "exact-barrel",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In order to train the VAMPNet transformations, we set up data loaders."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "functional-motel",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:43.293722Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:43.288954Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from torch.utils.data import DataLoader\n",
    "\n",
    "loader_train = DataLoader(train_data, batch_size=10000, shuffle=True)\n",
    "loader_val = DataLoader(val_data, batch_size=len(val_data), shuffle=False)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "explicit-bookmark",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And train!"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "reduced-leave",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-23T08:31:05.732250Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-23T08:30:45.717031Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "VAMPNet epoch:   0%|          | 0/30 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model = vampnet.fit(loader_train, n_epochs=30,\n",
    "                    validation_loader=loader_val, progress=tqdm).fetch_model()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "abstract-learning",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can visualize the progression of train and validation scores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "nonprofit-admission",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-22T16:43:47.800103Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-22T16:43:47.639186Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.loglog(*vampnet.train_scores.T, label='training')\n",
    "plt.loglog(*vampnet.validation_scores.T, label='validation')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('step')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('score')\n",
    "plt.legend();"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ongoing-refrigerator",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Given the trained model, we can transform our data and visualize the state probability in the $(\\phi, \\psi)$ plane."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "radio-column",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-22T16:43:55.708372Z",
     "start_time": "2021-03-22T16:43:50.750856Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 864x1152 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "state_probabilities = model.transform(data[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "f, axes = plt.subplots(3, 2, figsize=(12, 16))\n",
    "for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flatten()):\n",
    "    ax.scatter(*dihedral[0][::5].T, c=state_probabilities[..., i][::5])\n",
    "    ax.set_title(f'State {i+1}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "convertible-coordinator",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "One can also have a look at the assignment probability ranges that are produced by the forward lobe"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "annoying-means",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "state_probabilities = model.transform(data[0])\n",
    "for ix, (mini, maxi) in enumerate(zip(np.min(state_probabilities, axis=0), \n",
    "                                      np.max(state_probabilities, axis=0))):\n",

   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "macro-dakota",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "as well as cluster in the transformed space and assign each frame to its cluster center by taking the crisp assignment. Note that this step could also be performed by clustering with a potentially larger number of clusters."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "universal-modeling",
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2021-03-22T16:52:31.220670Z",

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "assignments = state_probabilities.argmax(1)\n",
    "plt.scatter(*dihedral[0].T, c=assignments, s=5, alpha=.1)\n",
    "plt.title('Transformed state assignments');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "joined-cursor",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With the transform we can obtain a VAMP model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "together-conflict",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "VAMP-2 score under lag 10: s = 3.28\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from deeptime.decomposition import VAMP\n",
    "\n",
    "vamp_estimator = VAMP(lagtime=10, observable_transform=model)\n",
    "vamp = vamp_estimator.fit(data).fetch_model()\n",
    "print(f\"VAMP-2 score under lag 10: s = {vamp.score(2).round(2)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "rational-sitting",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We may also evaluate the implied timescales to get an indication under which lagtime the data behaves Markovian, i.e., the region in which the implied timescales are flat. The timescales under the gray area are faster than the lagtime, meaning the corresponding processes have decayed and are no longer resolved by the model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "qualified-cherry",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "74f573fdc12b4fae99889c7dc8867560",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0/200 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "lagtimes = np.arange(1, 201, dtype=np.int32)\n",
    "timescales = []\n",
    "for lag in tqdm(lagtimes):\n",
    "    ts = VAMP(lagtime=lag, observable_transform=model).fit(data).fetch_model().timescales(k=5)\n",
    "    timescales.append(ts)\n",
    "    \n",
    "f, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1)\n",
    "ax.semilogy(lagtimes, timescales)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('lagtime')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('timescale / step')\n",
    "ax.fill_between(lagtimes, ax.get_ylim()[0]*np.ones(len(lagtimes)), lagtimes, alpha=0.5, color='grey');"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "tribal-stereo",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We may also perform a Chapman-Kolmogorov test. It is a relaxation experiment which, starting from each individual major process, checks how it evolves with respect to lagtime vs. estimating a new model at higher lagtime. If they show good agreement, this further validates that the data behaves Markovian at the chosen lagtime."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "id": "reserved-glass",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "validator = vamp_estimator.chapman_kolmogorov_validator(mlags=20)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "usual-acoustic",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It is important to choose `n_jobs=1` in case of VAMPNets to avoid serialization issues between otherwise spawned threads and trained PyTorch lobes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "id": "public-sampling",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0
      },
      "text/plain": [
       "  0%|          | 0/19 [00:00<?, ?it/s]"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cktest = validator.fit(data, n_jobs=1, progress=tqdm).fetch_model()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bridal-official",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let us visualize the CKTest based on the Koopman model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "fourth-sense",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 25 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_states = len(vamp.singular_values)\n",
    "\n",
    "tau = cktest.lagtimes[1]\n",
    "steps = len(cktest.lagtimes)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(n_states, n_states, sharex=True, sharey=True, constrained_layout=True)\n",
    "for i in range(n_states):\n",
    "    for j in range(n_states):\n",
    "        pred = ax[i][j].plot(cktest.lagtimes, cktest.predictions[:, i, j], color='b')\n",
    "        est = ax[i][j].plot(cktest.lagtimes, cktest.estimates[:, i, j], color='r', linestyle='--')\n",
    "        ax[i][j].set_title(str(i+1)+ '->' +str(j+1),\n",
    "                                       fontsize='small')\n",
    "ax[0][0].set_ylim((-0.1,1.1));\n",
    "ax[0][0].set_xlim((0, steps*tau));\n",
    "ax[0][0].axes.get_xaxis().set_ticks(np.round(np.linspace(0, steps*tau, 3)));\n",
    "fig.legend([pred[0], est[0]], [\"Predictions\", \"Estimates\"], 'lower center', ncol=2, \n",
    "           bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.1));"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "north-wallpaper",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We may also estimate a Bayesian MSM from the crisp assignments and perform a CKTest:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 20,
   "id": "shaped-lancaster",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "application/vnd.jupyter.widget-view+json": {
       "model_id": "",
       "version_major": 2,
       "version_minor": 0

    "from deeptime.markov import TransitionCountEstimator\n",
    "from deeptime.markov.msm import BayesianMSM\n",
    "\n",
    "counts = TransitionCountEstimator(lagtime=10, count_mode='effective').fit(assignments).fetch_model()\n",
    "bmsm = BayesianMSM().fit(counts)\n",
    "\n",
    "validator = bmsm.chapman_kolmogorov_validator(n_metastable_sets=6, mlags=10)\n",
    "cktest = validator.fit(assignments, progress=tqdm).fetch_model()\n",
    "\n",
    "n_states = len(vamp.singular_values)\n",
    "\n",
    "tau = cktest.lagtimes[1]\n",
    "steps = len(cktest.lagtimes)\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(n_states, n_states, sharex=True, sharey=True, constrained_layout=True)\n",
    "for i in range(n_states):\n",
    "    for j in range(n_states):\n",
    "        pred = ax[i][j].plot(cktest.lagtimes, cktest.predictions[:, i, j], color='b')\n",
    "        est = ax[i][j].plot(cktest.lagtimes, cktest.estimates[:, i, j], color='r', linestyle='--')\n",
    "        ax[i][j].set_title(str(i+1)+ '->' +str(j+1),\n",
    "                                       fontsize='small')\n",
    "        ax[i][j].fill_between(cktest.lagtimes, cktest.predictions_conf[0][:, i, j], \n",
    "                              cktest.predictions_conf[1][:, i, j], color='r', alpha=0.2)\n",
    "ax[0][0].set_ylim((-0.1,1.1));\n",
    "ax[0][0].set_xlim((0, steps*tau));\n",
    "ax[0][0].axes.get_xaxis().set_ticks(np.round(np.linspace(0, steps*tau, 3)));\n",
    "fig.legend([pred[0], est[0]], [\"Predictions\", \"Estimates\"], 'lower center', ncol=2, \n",
    "           bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.1));"
   ]
  }
